Parents:
For those who think the virtual instruction option is a better fit for your family, you do not need to declare that now. We will post a Virtual Instruction Application soon.

Please understand that we don't have every detail figured out just yet regarding the 2020-2021 school year but we are working on it. Our staff is working on many "what if" situations. We are not trying to hide anything. We will post information as it is finalized.
We appreciate your understanding and compassion for the task at hand.

post_text:
At this time, it is the intention of ERPS to return to school on August 13th in-person with accommodations including, but not limited to:
--School appropriate face coverings will be required for all students and staff
--Social distancing where possible
--Daily temperature checks
--Enhanced hygiene and sanitation practices

There is a virtual instruction option that parents may choose if in-person instruction does not fit the needs of the student.

The school board and administration will continue to observe and monitor the COVID-19 situation in El Reno. If conditions warrant, the school board may decide on July 28th to move to either the Blended Learning or Remote Learning model as described in the approved framework (see link below) to ensure the safety of students, parents, and staff.

https://5il.co/i8s2

post_text:
ERPS students, parents and community,
Due to the enormous amount of questions and information regarding how COVID-19 is affecting ERPS, we have created an FAQ document so that all of our responses are centralized.
If you have a question, please submit it to us by Facebook Messenger and NOT in the comments so we can keep all of our responses within this document.
As the situation that we are dealing with changes so rapidly, so too may our responses. We will post updates to this document as it is needed.

post_text:
ERPS will open our shelters tonight due to the potential of tornadoes overnight. We know that many in our community rely solely on the shelters for protection and have no other option. Please know that the school will have no liability if you choose to use the shelters regarding potential exposure to anyone who is ill. The shelters are large and there is a good chance you can still practice a 3' - 6' distance to others outside your household.
We implore the community to utilize common sense and compassion in dealing with others in attendance and ask everyone to carry out your own trash when you leave.
Thank you for your cooperation!
